Unexpected Consequences
While the decline in birth rates has a known impact on national economic growth, tax revenues, health spending and immigration policy, there have also been some unexpected consequences in Singapore.
The government is trying not to build so many small houses.
For example, she began to influence the real estate business.
The Urban Development Authority has started to regulate the number of small dwellings known as "boot boxes", which can be built in certain urban zones.
These apartments have an area of 46 square meters and have had great success in the shop.
However, there is concern that these apartments can promote youthful lifestyles and discourage developers from building large family homes.
